===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|now|_|historical}} [[ten|Ten]] [[thousand]]; 10,000.  {{defdate|from 16th c.}}
# A countless [[number]] or [[multitude]] (of specified things). {{defdate|from 16th c.}}
#: ''Earth hosts a '''myriad''' of animals.''
 
===Usage notes===
Used as an adjective (see below), myriad requires neither an article before it nor a preposition after. For this reason, some consider the usage described in sense 2, above, wherein 'myriad' acts as a noun in an adjectival group, to be [[tautological]], because the adjectival usage dispenses with the article and preposition (see sense 2, below).

